body.name: Lexar 128GB JumpDrive S80 USB 3.1 Flash Drive for Storage Expansion and Backup, Up To 150MB/s Read, Black (LJDS080128G-BNBNU)
deliveryMessages: FREE delivery Tuesday, February 20 on orders shipped by Amazon over $35
features: Stores and transfers content faster with high-speed USB 3.1 performance
Write speeds up to 10x faster than standard USB 2.0 drives
Protective, retractable design and securely protects files using an advanced security software with 256-bit AES encryption
USB 3.1 (Gen 1) compatible; backwards compatible with USB 3.0 and 2.0 devices
body.description: The high-performance Lexar JumpDrive S80 USB 3.1 Flash Drive allows you to quickly and securely transfer photos, videos, and files with speeds up to 150MB/s read and 60MB/s write. Now you can quickly transfer a 3GB 4K movie clip in less than 1 minute, compared to the 4 minutes it takes using a standard USB 2.0 drive. Available in a variety of capacities from 32GB-256GB, this drive also has advanced security software to help give you peace of mind knowing your files are safe. It’s also backward-compatible with USB 3.0 and 2.0 devices, providing added versatility. Three-year limited product support.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A lot of storage from a trusted manufacturer
reviews.reviewText: These USB drives are my new favorite. They can store a lot of data and the write speed is fine. I'm not a snob when it comes to these things, I just need it to work and it does.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I kind of wish there was a way of covering the exposed USB plug (other than pulling it down into the case) but otherwise, this jump drive works well. I've bought other Lexar portable drives, and they've all worked great for years. So many other companies produce portable drives that stop working in a short time. When I buy Lexar, I buy quality and dependability.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works for Me
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as the third member of a backup set; the first two were bought locally because they were on sale. So I actually have a couple of months experience with them.I am using them to back up my System Backup, so I had to format that NTFS to get around the FAT 4GB file size limit. This means that my remarks on speed are for NTFS-formatted drives only.The write speed ... If you look at the details, the write speed varies from 0 to 64 MB/s or so. Actual testing shows that the overall speed is pretty much the same as my Ethernet, which chugs along at a steady 10-12 MB/s. So the average is about 10-12 MB/s. This is using a USB 3.0 port.The read speed, measured using a USB 2.0 port since that is all the Notebook involved has, is also around 60 MB/s, but is quite steady. However, on two occasions, after the first quarter or third of the file was transferred, the speed dropped precipitously. I have no idea why.Reliability does not appear to be an issue, at least so far.I'm not sure what "warmth" means. It does heat up a bit when writing, but not (IMHO) excessively. It provides no emotional support that I can detect.Th

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good feel, Great speed!
reviews.reviewText: Not the strangest Flash Drive design I have used to open and close it, since you have to push the bottom while holding the top. Speed testing others have done do match what I got, make sure to check these to ensure you did not get a fake one with the way Amazon sells products now.Biggest thing you may notice is when moving a large amount of files or large sizes is the flash drive works like a toll booth where your truck of data will go through one load at a time when a large amount tries to go through. It gets portioned down and you can see the progress move in chunks. Not a major negative at all as the data transfers quick, but it does look funny when moving a few gigs of documents and seeing what looks like a laggy transfer.Great speeds if not a bootleg!
